**Performance Bottlenecks**:
- Creates a new RegExp object for EVERY transaction (line 212) - regex compilation is expensive
- Linear scan of results array to check if transaction already added (lines 217-223)
- Unnecessary regex escaping and compilation overhead per transaction

**Current Code Pattern**:
```typescript
for (const transaction of transactions) {
  const pattern = new RegExp(query.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\]\\]/g, "\\$&"), "i");  // Compile for every txn
