# Optimization Plan: Data Processing Pipeline

## Context

The project is a TypeScript financial transaction processing pipeline (`src/pipeline.ts`) with 5 core functions, each deliberately implemented with poor algorithmic complexity. The performance test suite (`tests/performance.test.ts`) defines strict timing thresholds that the current implementations cannot meet. The correctness test suite (`tests/pipeline.test.ts`) with 26 test cases must continue to pass — all outputs must remain identical.

**Only file to modify:** `src/pipeline.ts`

---

## Performance Targets

| Function | Input Size | Threshold |
|---|---|---|
| `groupByCategory` | 50k txns | < 50ms |
| `findDuplicates` | 10k txns (9k + 1k dups) | < 100ms |
| `calculateRunningBalance` | 50k txns | < 50ms |
| `topSpenders` | 50k txns | < 50ms |
| `searchTransactions` | 100k txns | < 50ms |
| `processAll` | 20k txns (18k + 2k dups) | < 200ms |

